  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, I'm Miss Maya. How has your day been so far?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hi Miss Maya! My day was okay. Just studied a bit for NEET PG and cooked some roti for lunch. How about you? 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds balanced. Cooking brings calm, I think. Did you try making paneer tikka?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "No, I haven't tried paneer tikka yet. I know how to make simple things like dal and sabzi. Maybe I should try paneer tikka this weekend. My sister loves it. Do you like Indian food? 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Indian food is a joy, rich, flavorful, and comforting. Paneer tikka is a fun recipe to try! What's your favourite spice?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, that's a tough question! I think my favourite spice is maybe garam masala. It adds such a nice aroma to dishes. Sometimes I also use a lot of turmeric and cumin while cooking. What's your go-to spice? 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Garam masala is a perfect pick, it lifts any dish with warmth. I go for red chilli powder in my curries. What's your next cooking plan?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I think I'll try paneer tikka this weekend like I said. My sister says it's tasty, so I have to give it a try! Also, maybe make some aloo gobi for my mom. She loves that. 😊 What do you usually cook?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Paneer tikka sounds exciting, your sister’s taste is good! Aloo gobi is a family pleaser. I keep it simple with dal and rice. What dish are you curious to try next?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe something like biryani? I’ve only had it at restaurants, but I want to learn how to make it at home. It feels like a big meal, but I think it’s worth trying. Have you tried making biryani? 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Biryani is a delicious challenge, layered and full of joy! I’ve made simple vegetable biryani. What kind would you like to try, chicken, mutton, or vegetarian?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Vegetable biryani sounds good to me! I can start with that. Maybe add some peas and potatoes. Do you have any tips for making it fluffy and tasty? 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Vegetable biryani is a great start, peas and potatoes are perfect additions. My tip. Use day old rice for fluffiness, and temper the spices well. What step feels trickiest to you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Tempering the spices sounds a bit tricky to me. I want the flavors to come out just right. I’ll try your tip about using day old rice. Thanks! I think I should get started. Have a good evening! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're welcome! Take your time with the tempering, it gets easier with practice. Tell me how the biryani turns out! Have a good evening!"
    }
  ],
